5:
He is secure at all times,\q but your righteous decrees are too high for him;
\q he snorts at all his enemies.


\q

8:
He waits in ambush near the villages;\q in the secret places he murders the innocent;
\q his eyes look for some helpless victim.
\q

14:
You have taken notice, for you always see the one who inflicts the misery and sorrow.\q The helpless entrusts himself to you;
\q you rescue the fatherless.


\q
